00:52:01.100 --> 00:52:09.060
<v John>I still encounter this like, oh, yes, if we could all go live in our Schwarzwalds and like make our own cabinets, you know.</v>

00:52:09.060 --> 00:52:19.640
<v Nate>You can see why he's really attractive for certain versions of contemporary theory because the project is at some level he wants to accommodate difference or relations,</v>

